1️⃣ Tween Teleport (Smooth Move – Most Reliable)

Instead of instantly teleporting, you slide there really fast so the server accepts it.

local TweenService = game:GetService("TweenService")

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local char = player.Character or player.CharacterAdded:Wait()
local root = char:WaitForChild("HumanoidRootPart")

local target = Vector3.new(5000, 50, 5000) -- where you want to go

local distance = (root.Position - target).Magnitude
local speed = 300 -- studs per second
local time = distance / speed

local tween = TweenService:Create(
    root,
    TweenInfo.new(time, Enum.EasingStyle.Linear),
    {CFrame = CFrame.new(target)}
)

tween:Play()

✅ Harder for the server to detect
✅ Works for long distance
❌ Slower than instant TP

2️⃣ Step Teleport (Jump in Small Steps)

Move in small chunks repeatedly instead of one giant teleport.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local char = player.Character
local root = char:WaitForChild("HumanoidRootPart")

local target = Vector3.new(5000,50,5000)

while (root.Position - target).Magnitude > 10 do
    root.CFrame = root.CFrame + (target - root.Position).Unit * 80
    task.wait()
end

root.CFrame = CFrame.new(target)

✅ Bypasses many anti-teleports
✅ Works farther than normal TP

3️⃣ Velocity Launch Method

Instead of teleporting, shoot yourself there physically.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local char = player.Character
local root = char:WaitForChild("HumanoidRootPart")

local target = Vector3.new(5000,50,5000)

local velocity = Instance.new("BodyVelocity")
velocity.MaxForce = Vector3.new(1e9,1e9,1e9)
velocity.Velocity = (target - root.Position).Unit * 500
velocity.Parent = root

task.wait(2)

velocity:Destroy()

✅ Server sees real movement
✅ Good bypass sometimes

4️⃣ Seat / Vehicle Teleport (Very Powerful)

If you sit in a seat, the server often trusts the seat’s position more.

local vehicle = workspace.Vehicles:FindFirstChild(game.Players.LocalPlayer:GetAttribute("spawnedVehicleid"))

if vehicle then
    vehicle:PivotTo(CFrame.new(5000,50,5000))
end

✅ Often bypasses rubber-band
✅ Best for cars

5️⃣ Network Ownership Method (Advanced)

If you own physics for a part, you can move it easier.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local char = player.Character
local root = char:WaitForChild("HumanoidRootPart")

root:SetNetworkOwner(player)

root.CFrame = CFrame.new(5000,50,5000)
